title: New Caledonia Imports
description: Imports in New Caledonia increased to 46211 XPF Million in September from 34457 XPF Million in August of 2022. Imports in New Caledonia averaged 18079.88 XPF Million from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 46211 XPF Million in September of 2022 and a record low of 5796 XPF Million in February of 1995. New Caledonia’s main imports are fuel, vehicles, pharmaceutical products, coal, automatic data processing machines, turbojets, wine and tires. New Caledonia’s main imports partners are France, Singapore, Australia, China, Germany, South Korea, Japan, Malaysia and the United Kingdom. This page provides the latest reported value for - New Caledonia Imports - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: ISEE, New Caledonia
